project.description:
This ant build file is an helper script that defines the webtest tasks, runs the tests and formats the generated results to html. It is intended to be called from bin/runWebtest.{bat|sh}
Mandatory parameters: webtest.testfile: the file to run webtest.testdir: the absolute path to the directory where the test file is located (and where the results will be generated)
Optional parameters: webtest.config.skipCleanup: file existing in output dir should not be deleted before test started webtest.home: the absolute path to the webtest distribution (needed to find the resource for the xslt)
